@cevich don't know if you can see this page: https://copr.fedorainfracloud.org/coprs/rhcontainerbot/podman-next/package/podman/ but it has a field `Committish: main` which records the upstream branch to build from. When we want to build from v4.0, we just gotta switch that value over there. /cc @mheon @baude.

@cevich if you need admin access to the copr repo, add yourself to https://copr.fedorainfracloud.org/coprs/rhcontainerbot/podman-next/permissions/ and I can approve you . Edit: matt and brent are admins there already, so it's not blocked on my pto.

@cevich RE: `Test build RPM` I'm not too sure, i think the existing task uses some magic in `hack/` + makefile targets or something, yes? Not sure it's easily transferrable to `.autocopr/podman.spec`
